properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 8 at 1:29PM PST until February 9 at 8:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Gusty North to East Wind Sunday...

.Low pressure brings a period of strong north to east wind over
portions of interior Northern California Sunday. Wind begins to
increase later tonight, with the strongest wind Sunday. Highest
wind speeds are expected along the west side of the Sacramento
Valley extending into the Coastal Range, and over portions of the
Sierra Nevada. Wind speeds decrease Sunday night, but remain
breezy into Monday.

* WHAT...North to east wind 20 to 35 mph. Wind gusts up to 50
mph possible in the Central Valley Sunday. Wind gusts locally
up to 60 mph or higher in Coastal Range and Sierra Nevada.

* WHERE...Sacramento Valley, Carquinez Strait and Delta,
Northern San Joaquin Valley, Coastal range from Western Shasta
County to Lake County, Western Plumas County and West Slopes
of the Northern Sierra Nevada.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 8 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty wind could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and power outages may result.
Difficult driving conditions for small and high profile
vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Northerly wind may cause downed trees in
the Delta region due to non-prevailing wind direction. Strong
easterly wind could impact outdoor recreational activities in
the Sierra Nevada.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 8 PM PST SUNDAY
